# Scaffold Module Skill

When invoked with `@scaffold-module {module-name} {service}`, create a complete module structure following Clean Architecture patterns.

## Purpose

Quickly bootstrap new feature modules with consistent structure, reducing boilerplate and ensuring architectural compliance.

## Prerequisites

Before scaffolding:
1. Verify the service exists
2. Check ARCHITECTURE.md for service-specific patterns
3. Review existing modules for consistency

## Module Structure to Create

```
services/{service}/src/modules/{module-name}/
├── {module-name}.module.ts          # NestJS module definition
├── application/                      # Application layer
│   ├── {module-name}.service.ts     # Business logic service
│   └── use-cases/                   # Optional: specific use cases
├── domain/                          # Domain layer
│   ├── entities/
│   │   └── {module-name}.entity.ts  # Domain entity
│   ├── interfaces/
│   │   └── {module-name}.repository.interface.ts
│   └── value-objects/               # Optional: value objects
├── infrastructure/                  # Infrastructure layer
│   └── {module-name}.repository.ts  # Repository implementation
├── presentation/                    # Presentation layer
│   └── {module-name}.controller.ts  # REST controller
└── dto/                             # Data transfer objects
    ├── create-{module-name}.dto.ts
    ├── update-{module-name}.dto.ts
    └── {module-name}-response.dto.ts
```

## File Templates

### Module File (`{module-name}.module.ts`)

```typescript
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';
import { {ModuleName}Controller } from './presentation/{module-name}.controller';
import { {ModuleName}Service } from './application/{module-name}.service';
import { {ModuleName}Repository } from './infrastructure/{module-name}.repository';

/**
 * {ModuleName} Module
 * 
 * Handles {description of module purpose}
 * 
 * @module {ModuleName}Module
 */
@Module({
  imports: [],
  controllers: [{ModuleName}Controller],
  providers: [
    {ModuleName}Service,
    {ModuleName}Repository,
  ],
  exports: [{ModuleName}Service],
})
export class {ModuleName}Module {}
```

### Service File (`application/{module-name}.service.ts`)

```typescript
import { Injectable, Logger } from '@nestjs/common';
import { {ModuleName}Repository } from '../infrastructure/{module-name}.repository';

/**
 * {ModuleName} Service
 * 
 * Business logic for {module purpose}
 */
@Injectable()
export class {ModuleName}Service {
  private readonly logger = new Logger({ModuleName}Service.name);

  constructor(
    private readonly repository: {ModuleName}Repository,
  ) {}

  // TODO: Implement service methods
}
```

### Controller File (`presentation/{module-name}.controller.ts`)

```typescript
import { Controller, Get, Post, Body, Param, Put, Delete } from '@nestjs/common';
import { ApiTags, ApiOperation, ApiResponse } from '@nestjs/swagger';
import { {ModuleName}Service } from '../application/{module-name}.service';
import { Create{ModuleName}Dto } from '../dto/create-{module-name}.dto';
import { Update{ModuleName}Dto } from '../dto/update-{module-name}.dto';

/**
 * {ModuleName} Controller
 * 
 * REST API endpoints for {module purpose}
 */
@ApiTags('{module-name}')
@Controller('{module-name}')
export class {ModuleName}Controller {
  constructor(private readonly service: {ModuleName}Service) {}

  // TODO: Implement controller endpoints
}
```

## Test Files to Create

```
services/{service}/test/{module-name}.e2e-spec.ts
```

### E2E Test Template

```typescript
import { Test, TestingModule } from '@nestjs/testing';
import { INestApplication } from '@nestjs/common';
import * as request from 'supertest';
import { AppModule } from '../src/app.module';

describe('{ModuleName} (e2e)', () => {
  let app: INestApplication;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    const moduleFixture: TestingModule = await Test.createTestingModule({
      imports: [AppModule],
    }).compile();

    app = moduleFixture.createNestApplication();
    await app.init();
  });

  afterEach(async () => {
    await app.close();
  });

  // TODO: Add E2E test cases
  describe('GET /{module-name}', () => {
    it('should return list of {module-name}s', () => {
      return request(app.getHttpServer())
        .get('/{module-name}')
        .expect(200);
    });
  });
});
```

## Post-Scaffold Actions

1. **Register module** in `app.module.ts`
2. **Update ARCHITECTURE.md** with new module documentation
3. **Update CONTRACTS.md** with API endpoints
4. **Run linter** to check for issues

## Required Output Format

```
## Module Scaffolded: {module-name} in {service}

### Created Files
- [x] {module-name}.module.ts
- [x] application/{module-name}.service.ts
- [x] domain/entities/{module-name}.entity.ts
- [x] infrastructure/{module-name}.repository.ts
- [x] presentation/{module-name}.controller.ts
- [x] dto/create-{module-name}.dto.ts
- [x] dto/update-{module-name}.dto.ts
- [x] test/{module-name}.e2e-spec.ts

### Next Steps
1. Register {ModuleName}Module in app.module.ts
2. Define entity properties in {module-name}.entity.ts
3. Implement DTO validation with class-validator
4. Add service methods
5. Implement controller endpoints
6. Write E2E tests

### Update Documentation
Run `@docs-update` to update ARCHITECTURE.md and CONTRACTS.md
```

## Example Usage

```
User: @scaffold-module user-preferences api

AI: [Verifies services/api/ exists]
    [Creates module structure]
    [Creates all template files]
    [Creates E2E test file]
    [Outputs summary]
```
